
-----------------
JavaScript Client
-----------------

* Compile & Run the JavaScript client

    As usual, with a new compilation task

    ant compile

    ant compile-gwt

    ant compile-wavejsclient-dev

    ant run-server (or ./run-server.sh)


* Usage example

    See war/examples/wavejs.html

    or

    Add following <scripts> sections into the head section of your html file (use the right host in the src attribute):

    <script type="text/javascript" src="wavejsclient/wavejsclient.nocache.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">

           // start up Wave infrastructure an open a wave
           function onWaveJSClientReady() {

             wavejs.startSession("http://localhost:9898", "tim", "tim",
                    function() {
                      alert("Login succesfull!");


                      wavejs.openWave("local.net/c+YLvAtVjZjAA",
                               function() {
                                    alert("Wave opened succesfully!");
                                },
                                 function() {
                                  alert("Wave open failure!");
                                });


                    },function() {
                      alert("Login failed!");
                    });
           };

    </script>



----------
GWT Client
----------

* Generating Maven artifacts for integration with third apps


Run install-mvn-artifacts.sh to generate and install the maven artifacts in the local repo.

These are the mvn dependencies:


    <!-- GWT modules for building a Wave based app -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.waveprotocol</groupId>
        <artifactId>compact-client</artifactId>
        <version>0.4-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.waveprotocol</groupId>
        <artifactId>compact-client-src</artifactId>
        <version>0.4-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.waveprotocol</groupId>
        <artifactId>proto</artifactId>
        <version>0.4-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.waveprotocol</groupId>
        <artifactId>proto-src</artifactId>
        <version>0.4-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.waveprotocol</groupId>
        <artifactId>proto-msg</artifactId>
        <version>0.4-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>